# Phase 31: Blank Screen Settings Implementation

I have successfully implemented the "Blank Screen" preset settings based on your approved implementation plan.

## Overview of Changes

> [!NOTE]
> The Blank Screen settings operate seamlessly within the existing Presentation Settings framework, functioning alongside the Song and Scripture settings.

### 1. Database and Provider
- Expanded the `PresentationSettings` Isar model to store blank-specific visual styles:
  - Aspect Ratio (`blankAspectRatio`, `blankCustomWidth`, `blankCustomHeight`)
  - Background Properties (`blankBackgroundColor`, `blankBackgroundImage`, `isBlankImageEnabled`, `isBlankTransparent`)
- Auto-generated the required Isar bindings using `build_runner`.
- Updated `presentation_settings_provider.dart` to support updating the new properties depending on the selected tab index (0: Song, 1: Scripture, 2: Blank Screen) and providing fallbacks.

### 2. Settings User Interface
- Added a "Blank Screen" tab to the `SegmentedButton` in `presentation_settings_dialog.dart`.
- The Typography (Title and Body) sections are correctly hidden when the "Blank Screen" tab is selected.
- The Preview Window dynamically simulates a blank screen when on the "Blank Screen" tab.
- Saving changes updates the specific blank screen properties in the database.

### 3. Live Monitor Rendering
- Updated `projector_view.dart` to check if `activeSlideText == ""` (a blank slide). When true, the view uses the blank screen configurations (aspect ratio, custom sizes, background colors, and images) rather than falling back to black.
- Modified the aspect ratio calculations in `live_projector_pane.dart` to also pass `isBlank: true` for empty slides. This ensures the live monitor pane dynamically adjusts its letterbox bounds specifically based on the Blank Screen aspect ratio if a blank slide is selected on the dashboard.

## Verification
- Code successfully builds with `flutter analyze` returning zero regressions.
- Isar models generated correctly.
- Application logic seamlessly adapts the UI based on whether a real slide or a blank slide is projected on Monitor 1 and Monitor 2.
